channel.title: Sorry for the second post
channel.description: Ok, so I have the client for deltascape, if I edit the class8 file in there, when I run the server from the source, will it automatically access the class8 file? So I guess my question is what does the client file do for me, and how does it affect my server.

item.title: Sorry for the second post
item.dc:creator: @jailed jailed
item.description:
@jailed wrote:

After you’ve put ints in the class8.java, compile, add the models to the ‘model’ folder for the custom unless it’s a re-color, then run the client, log in and type:

add model #####
Replace ##### with the model id, and do this for all the models that comes with the custom. NOTE: Do NOT use '::' before 'add model #####', only enter 'add model #####' this is NOT a command.

@fuery0w wrote:

Client is used to PLAY your server. You need to compile after you change the class8 file. You actually have to compile after you change ANYTHING in the Client folder and Source.
